    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="9">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301975">Figure 75</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301975" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301975" filename="../figg13/G1301975.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 75. Input Shaft Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing retaining snap ring from the groove in the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301976">Figure 76</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301976" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301976" filename="../figg13/G1301976.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 76. Remove Bearing Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a rubber maul on the input shaft to cock the bearing in the bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301977">Figure 77</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301977" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301977" filename="../figg13/G1301977.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 77. Cock Bearing in Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive the input shaft toward the rear of the transmission, through the bearing as far as
                possible (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301978">Figure 78</hotlnk>). Pull input shaft toward the front of the transmission to
                unseat the bearing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301978" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301978" filename="../figg13/G1301978.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 78. Drive Input Shaft Toward Rear of Transmission</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pry bars to complete removal of the bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301979">Figure 79</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301979" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301979" filename="../figg13/G1301979.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 79. Use Pry Bars to Complete Removal of Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear spacer and snap ring (inset,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301980">Figure 80</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301980" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301980" filename="../figg13/G1301980.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 80. Remove Drive Gear Spacer and Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull input shaft forward and out of the drive gear and case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301981">Figure 81</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301981" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301981" filename="../figg13/G1301981.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 81. Pull Input Shaft Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the bushing in the pocket of the input shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301982">Figure 82</hotlnk>). Replace if worn.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301982" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301982" filename="../figg13/G1301982.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 82. Check Bushing in Pocket of Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the main drive gear from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301983">Figure 83</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301983" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301983" filename="../figg13/G1301983.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 83. Remove Main Drive Gear From Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
